			<ns0:name>cbiffle@google.com</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/cbiffle@google.com/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">NaCl binaries are required to have room between the end-of-text and start-of-data -- 32 bytes of room, to be precise (see NACL_HALT_SLED_SIZE in nacl_config.h).

Our old ARM linker script ensured that this was true, but the current PNaCl-based toolchain has regressed.  We need to fix the linker script to ensure that the text and data never fall immediately on either side of a 64KiB boundary, so that we have room for the halt sled.  This bug may also affect non-ARM toolchains.

We have several binaries that fluctuate around 64KiB in size.  Until this is fixed, if any becomes exactly 64KiB, it will fail spectacularly.  This is what happened to simple_thread_test -- see background on issue 732.

(Assigning blindly to espindola@ since he's been working on the linker -- feel free to reassign.)</ns0:content><ns0:updated>2011-03-09T17:34:28.000Z</ns0:updated><ns0:published>2010-07-30T22:42:34.000Z</ns0:published><ns2:status>Fixed</ns2:status><ns2:owner>
